1
00:00:21,678 --> 00:00:25,807
[ZWORDER]
The universe is infinitely vast.

2
00:00:27,225 --> 00:00:32,022
[ZWORDER] An endless
expanse of silent lights.

3
00:00:32,105 --> 00:00:36,109
Stars die,
and new stars are born.

4
00:00:36,192 --> 00:00:39,195
An eternal cycle of life.

5
00:00:39,279 --> 00:00:44,284
Yes. The universe is alive.

6
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:45,952
It lives.

7
00:00:46,036 --> 00:00:48,288
It lives!

8
00:00:50,832 --> 00:00:55,712
[ZWORDER] And that is why
we will show it our love.

9
00:03:17,437 --> 00:03:19,189
[MEN groaning]

10
00:03:19,272 --> 00:03:21,024
[groaning]

11
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:24,152
[ZWORDER]
Empty.

12
00:03:24,235 --> 00:03:26,738
Truly empty.

13
00:03:26,821 --> 00:03:30,784
What meaning was there
in these men's lives?

14
00:03:34,412 --> 00:03:37,540
[ZWORDER]
To what end did they serve?

15
00:03:37,624 --> 00:03:40,460
What imagined purpose
could possibly justify

16
00:03:40,543 --> 00:03:41,711
such needless suffering?

17
00:03:41,795 --> 00:03:43,755
[MEN screaming]

18
00:03:43,838 --> 00:03:47,217
[ZWORDER] Love is the only
worthy aspiration.

19
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:50,345
A love which can purge
every last bit of suffering

20
00:03:50,428 --> 00:03:54,891
from this universe.
An infinite love!

21
00:03:57,227 --> 00:04:00,605
[ZWORDER]
Wouldn't you agree...

22
00:04:00,689 --> 00:04:02,399
...Teresa?

23
00:04:06,152 --> 00:04:09,322
[TERESA] Everything has
been predetermined.

24
00:04:09,406 --> 00:04:13,493
But... that does not
mean all is lost.

25
00:04:13,576 --> 00:04:20,417
Warriors of a distant star...
my hope now rests with you.

26
00:04:45,734 --> 00:04:47,402
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A]
All ships have warped out.

27
00:04:47,485 --> 00:04:49,612
Assuming deep battle formation.

28
00:04:55,243 --> 00:04:58,413
[UNCF OPERATOR 1B]
Prepare for ship-to-ship combat.

29
00:04:58,496 --> 00:04:59,914
[UNCF OPERATOR 1C]
Open data link.

30
00:04:59,998 --> 00:05:03,084
All radar operators monitor
for changes in grid display.

31
00:05:30,904 --> 00:05:32,405
[SERIZAWA]
It has been 60 days

32
00:05:32,489 --> 00:05:35,325
since the enemy occupation of
the floating continent began.

33
00:05:35,408 --> 00:05:37,118
The Gamilans have determined

34
00:05:37,202 --> 00:05:39,913
that the base staff
is already lost.

35
00:05:39,996 --> 00:05:42,874
They are now prepared to launch
a full-scale assault to expel

36
00:05:42,957 --> 00:05:46,419
the Gatlantean Fleet from the
Eighth Floating Continent Base.

37
00:05:46,503 --> 00:05:48,380
Earth Fleet will have
the honor of assisting

38
00:05:48,463 --> 00:05:51,966
the Gamilans in this endeavor
to reclaim their facility.

39
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:54,594
The Gamilan force will
attack as the vanguard.

40
00:05:54,678 --> 00:05:56,137
We will bring up
the rear to defeat

41
00:05:56,221 --> 00:05:58,473
any and all enemy ships
that slip past them.

42
00:05:58,556 --> 00:06:00,058
Happy hunting.

43
00:06:00,141 --> 00:06:02,560
[AIHARA] Armored Assault-type
Zoelguut-class vessels.

44
00:06:02,644 --> 00:06:06,314
Even on Gamilas, it'd be rare to
see three together in one place.

45
00:06:06,398 --> 00:06:07,816
Gather all the intel you can.

46
00:06:07,899 --> 00:06:09,442
Let's see if we can
size up their defenses

47
00:06:09,526 --> 00:06:10,985
while we have the chance
to see 'em up close--

48
00:06:11,069 --> 00:06:13,446
[KODAI]
Aihara.

49
00:06:13,530 --> 00:06:15,115
Gamilas is our ally now.

50
00:06:15,198 --> 00:06:18,326
We didn't come here
to spy on a friendly fleet.

51
00:06:18,410 --> 00:06:20,870
[AIHARA]
U-Uh. Yes, Captain Kodai!

52
00:06:20,954 --> 00:06:23,540
Taking support position behind
the Zoelguut-class vessels.

53
00:06:23,623 --> 00:06:25,291
[beeping]

54
00:06:47,230 --> 00:06:48,565
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A]
The enemy Gatlantean Fleet

55
00:06:48,648 --> 00:06:50,150
is deploying units
at all positions

56
00:06:50,233 --> 00:06:51,776
on the Eighth
Floating Continent.

57
00:06:51,860 --> 00:06:53,111
They're advancing
to our front...

58
00:06:53,194 --> 00:06:54,195
[UNCF OPERATOR 1B]
Transmission received

59
00:06:54,279 --> 00:06:55,905
from patrol and
surveillance unit:

60
00:06:55,989 --> 00:06:57,282
"Warning. Multiple firepower..."

61
00:06:57,365 --> 00:06:59,909
In position. Combined Fleet
is prepared to engage.

62
00:06:59,993 --> 00:07:02,162
Roger that. Let's stay sharp.

63
00:07:02,245 --> 00:07:04,789
Make sure there are no surprises
waiting for them out there.

64
00:07:04,873 --> 00:07:06,916
[UNCF OPERATOR 1C] First contact
with enemy unit imminent.

65
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,126
Preparing to engage.

66
00:07:08,209 --> 00:07:10,545
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A]
Earth Fleet advancing.

67
00:07:10,628 --> 00:07:12,630
[UNCF OPERATOR 1D]
The fleet has begun the attack.

68
00:07:12,714 --> 00:07:13,840
[MORI gasps]

69
00:07:30,690 --> 00:07:32,025
[UNCF OPERATOR 1C]
Taking heavy losses!

70
00:07:32,108 --> 00:07:33,026
[UNCF OPERATOR 1B]
Enemy advancing.

71
00:07:33,109 --> 00:07:35,153
Second wave incoming.

72
00:07:46,498 --> 00:07:50,085
[TODO]
Hm? What ship is that?

73
00:07:50,168 --> 00:07:51,753
[UNCF OPERATOR 1C]
ID confirmed:

74
00:07:51,836 --> 00:07:55,423
Ship K-47 of the 2nd Destroyer
Escort Fleet... the <i>Yunagi.</i>

75
00:07:55,507 --> 00:07:56,675
[MORI gasps]

76
00:07:56,758 --> 00:07:58,176
[RADAR OP. 1A]
Fighters launching from carrier!

77
00:07:58,259 --> 00:08:00,303
[KODAI]
Topside missiles... fire!

78
00:08:18,238 --> 00:08:20,990
[KODAI] Torpedoes at the ready!
Tubes one through four!

79
00:08:21,074 --> 00:08:24,369
Angle of aperture,
three degrees! Fire!

80
00:09:05,994 --> 00:09:08,329
Captain! Enemy fleet retreating!

81
00:09:08,413 --> 00:09:11,332
They're pulling back to
the floating continent.

82
00:09:11,416 --> 00:09:12,751
They're what?

83
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:19,299
They had us outgunned. Why
would they suddenly run away?

84
00:09:19,382 --> 00:09:22,302
[RADAR OP. 1A] Gamilan
fleet appears to be pursuing.

85
00:09:25,138 --> 00:09:26,806
Open a line to
the Gamilan flagship.

86
00:09:26,890 --> 00:09:28,058
Get me their captain.

87
00:09:28,141 --> 00:09:29,476
On it.

88
00:09:33,772 --> 00:09:35,565
[RADAR OP. 1A] Reading a
massive, unidentified object

89
00:09:35,648 --> 00:09:37,192
approaching the
Gatlantean fleet!

90
00:09:37,275 --> 00:09:38,610
What?

91
00:09:45,575 --> 00:09:48,453
Uh. What the hell is that thing?

92
00:10:20,694 --> 00:10:21,945
A ship?

93
00:10:22,028 --> 00:10:23,780
It's enormous.

94
00:10:50,056 --> 00:10:51,266
[RADAR OP. 1A]
The forward Gamilan fleet

95
00:10:51,349 --> 00:10:53,643
has been completely wiped out!

96
00:11:02,110 --> 00:11:04,696
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A] 6th and 7th
squadrons taking heavy losses!

97
00:11:04,779 --> 00:11:07,574
Have them pull back at once!

98
00:11:07,657 --> 00:11:12,704
Commander. I believe this
could be... an opportunity.

99
00:11:12,787 --> 00:11:13,913
[TODO]
Hm?

100
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,340
Ensure that no friendly vessels

101
00:11:23,423 --> 00:11:26,009
will be caught in the
line of fire. Not one.

102
00:11:26,092 --> 00:11:27,844
Then, you may proceed.

103
00:11:27,927 --> 00:11:29,262
Sir.

104
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:33,016
Priority command for
all deployed fleets!

105
00:11:33,099 --> 00:11:34,559
Initiate Plan A!

106
00:11:34,642 --> 00:11:38,355
All remaining ships, fall back
to designated positions.

107
00:11:38,438 --> 00:11:39,814
Plan A?

108
00:11:39,898 --> 00:11:41,191
What is that?

109
00:11:41,274 --> 00:11:42,650
I don't know.

110
00:11:42,734 --> 00:11:44,778
Looks like these were
encrypted files

111
00:11:44,861 --> 00:11:47,072
pre-installed on
the fleet network.

112
00:11:49,157 --> 00:11:53,620
But this is... It can't be!

113
00:11:53,703 --> 00:11:56,581
[COUNTDOWN]
24... 23... 22...

114
00:11:56,664 --> 00:11:58,500
...21... 20...

115
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:01,002
...19... 18... 17...

116
00:12:01,086 --> 00:12:03,880
Orders for Plan A:
2nd Destroyer Escort Fleet

117
00:12:03,963 --> 00:12:06,091
retreat to third warning
line immediately.

118
00:12:06,174 --> 00:12:08,426
[NANBU]
First I've heard of this.

119
00:12:08,510 --> 00:12:11,054
[COUNTDOWN]
...9... 8... 7...

120
00:12:11,137 --> 00:12:14,182
...6... 5... 4...

121
00:12:14,265 --> 00:12:16,101
...3... 2...

122
00:12:16,184 --> 00:12:17,602
...1...

123
00:12:21,147 --> 00:12:23,942
[RADAR OP. 1A] Reading extra-
dimensional energy emissions.

124
00:12:28,947 --> 00:12:30,240
[gasps]

125
00:12:54,556 --> 00:12:55,640
Uh. Wave Motion Gun?

126
00:12:55,724 --> 00:12:57,851
[NANBU]
Yeah, but, who fired it?

127
00:13:01,646 --> 00:13:03,648
[STARSHA]
Promise me you will be better.

128
00:13:03,732 --> 00:13:04,816
[KODAI gasps]

129
00:13:04,899 --> 00:13:06,735
[STARSHA]
Promise me you will be better.

130
00:13:06,818 --> 00:13:08,194
Swear that you won't ever repeat

131
00:13:08,278 --> 00:13:10,780
the same horrible
mistakes we made.

132
00:13:10,864 --> 00:13:12,991
[OKITA]
I give you my word.

133
00:13:13,074 --> 00:13:14,534
I give you my word.

134
00:13:14,617 --> 00:13:15,869
[KODAI grunts]

135
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:22,334
[SANADA]
Kodai, we have to face reality.

136
00:13:22,417 --> 00:13:24,919
The Earth was nearly
wiped out in the last war.

137
00:13:25,003 --> 00:13:27,047
If we're going to survive...

138
00:13:33,053 --> 00:13:35,597
[YAMANAMI] All ships, this is
Earth Federation Defense

139
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,599
Force Fleet Flagship, <i>Andromeda.</i>

140
00:13:37,682 --> 00:13:41,770
Destruction of the 8th Floating
Continent has been confirmed.

141
00:13:41,853 --> 00:13:44,689
We will now transition
into a mop-up operation.

142
00:13:44,773 --> 00:13:46,858
Earth-Gamilan Combined
Fleet vessels,

143
00:13:46,941 --> 00:13:49,652
remain on guard until
we give the all-clear.

144
00:13:49,736 --> 00:13:52,864
We of course applaud you for
your efforts to this point.

145
00:13:52,947 --> 00:13:54,240
Is this for real?

146
00:13:54,324 --> 00:13:57,202
This has gotta be some
kinda sick joke, right?

147
00:14:01,373 --> 00:14:04,000
The <i>Andromeda.</i>

148
00:14:04,084 --> 00:14:06,836
So it's already been completed.

149
00:14:16,429 --> 00:14:18,932
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A] <i>Andromeda</i> now
entering the combat area.

150
00:14:19,015 --> 00:14:20,684
Very impressive.

151
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:22,686
The Dispersion Wave Motion Gun.

152
00:14:22,769 --> 00:14:25,605
After our success here today,
perhaps the people of Gamilas

153
00:14:25,689 --> 00:14:28,441
will begin to see the
Earth in a new light.

154
00:14:28,525 --> 00:14:29,317
No doubt.

155
00:14:29,401 --> 00:14:31,361
Your enemies will, too.

156
00:14:35,156 --> 00:14:37,534
[ANDROMEDA CM 1A]
Enemy battleship spotted.

157
00:14:39,119 --> 00:14:40,829
Dead in the water.

158
00:14:41,830 --> 00:14:43,248
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A]
<i>Defiance</i> and <i>Saratoga</i>

159
00:14:43,331 --> 00:14:45,834
unable to continue
operations due to damage.

160
00:14:45,917 --> 00:14:47,168
They are requesting permission

161
00:14:47,252 --> 00:14:49,462
to return to Earth via
long distance warp.

162
00:14:49,546 --> 00:14:51,047
Permission granted.

163
00:14:51,131 --> 00:14:52,340
[MORI]
A Wave Motion Gun.

164
00:14:52,424 --> 00:14:53,550
[TODO]
Hm?

165
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:56,928
[MORI]
You built a Wave Motion Gun.

166
00:14:57,012 --> 00:14:59,139
How could you?

167
00:14:59,222 --> 00:15:02,559
Is this how we honor the promise
we made three years ago?

168
00:15:09,232 --> 00:15:10,483
[ANDROMEDA RADAR OP. 1A]
Enemy battleship's engine

169
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:11,609
has just fired up!

170
00:15:11,693 --> 00:15:13,445
Main gun, lock on target!

171
00:15:13,528 --> 00:15:15,447
[ANDROMEDA RADAR OP. 1A]
It's accelerating too quickly!

172
00:15:15,530 --> 00:15:19,492
[YAMANAMI] Belay that order.
Rear guns 3 and 4--fire!

173
00:15:21,578 --> 00:15:22,954
Fire!

174
00:15:28,293 --> 00:15:30,795
Gatlantean vessel closing
on us at high speed!

175
00:15:30,879 --> 00:15:33,298
What?! Veer hard to port!

176
00:15:34,924 --> 00:15:36,092
[KODAI grunts]

177
00:15:41,139 --> 00:15:41,848
[YAMANAMI grunts]

178
00:15:41,931 --> 00:15:43,183
You're sure about that?

179
00:15:43,266 --> 00:15:44,976
[YUNAGI RADAR OP. 1A]
Yes, sir! The enemy vessel

180
00:15:45,060 --> 00:15:48,355
followed the same trajectory
as <i>Defiance</i> and <i>Saratoga.</i>

181
00:15:48,438 --> 00:15:49,898
Emergency warp, now!

182
00:15:49,981 --> 00:15:52,150
We need to get back to Earth!

183
00:16:02,702 --> 00:16:05,372
[KIRYU] Enormous mass warping
out in outer lunar orbit!

184
00:16:05,455 --> 00:16:07,290
What?

185
00:16:07,374 --> 00:16:09,042
[KIRYU] Confirming <i>Saratoga</i> and
<i>Defiance</i> 's warp out signals

186
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,377
from the same point.

187
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:12,754
Object is thought to be
the Gatlantean battleship

188
00:16:12,837 --> 00:16:15,048
that warped from
the combat area.

189
00:16:15,131 --> 00:16:16,633
[SERIZAWA] What about
the defense satellite?

190
00:16:16,716 --> 00:16:19,219
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A]
Automated intercept has engaged!

191
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,268
[UNCF OPERATOR 1D]
Defense line has been breached!

192
00:16:27,352 --> 00:16:30,355
Gatlantean vessel...
now within lunar orbit!

193
00:16:30,438 --> 00:16:33,441
Will enter Earth atmosphere
in 400 seconds!

194
00:16:33,525 --> 00:16:35,568
Where is the projected
landing site?

195
00:16:35,652 --> 00:16:38,405
[KIRYU gasping]
It's here!

196
00:16:38,488 --> 00:16:39,656
[SERIZAWA gasps]

197
00:16:39,739 --> 00:16:43,201
So this is how Gatlantis
fights their battles.

198
00:16:49,290 --> 00:16:50,583
[OBSERVER 1A]
Mr. Serizawa.

199
00:16:50,667 --> 00:16:52,711
Please compose yourself,
sir, there is no time!

200
00:16:52,794 --> 00:16:55,755
Quickly! Give the order to
evacuate the capital region!

201
00:16:55,839 --> 00:16:57,382
[SERIZAWA]
It's hopeless.

202
00:16:57,465 --> 00:17:00,343
If something with that much mass
comes down at that speed,

203
00:17:00,427 --> 00:17:01,970
we're all doomed.

204
00:17:02,053 --> 00:17:03,263
Now Issuing the alert

205
00:17:03,346 --> 00:17:05,473
for the civilian evacuation
guidance program.

206
00:17:05,557 --> 00:17:08,226
Open all passages into
the old underground city.

207
00:17:08,309 --> 00:17:11,312
[KIRYU] New warp out signal
detected near enemy ship.

208
00:17:15,525 --> 00:17:16,860
[KIRYU]
ID K-47.

209
00:17:16,943 --> 00:17:17,777
The <i>Yunagi</i> !

210
00:17:17,861 --> 00:17:19,487
Kodai's here?

211
00:17:19,571 --> 00:17:21,114
[NANBU]
Enemy ship overhead!

212
00:17:21,197 --> 00:17:22,991
[AIHARA] It's on course
to hit the atmosphere!

213
00:17:23,074 --> 00:17:24,492
Main cannons at the ready!

214
00:17:24,576 --> 00:17:25,952
Fire!

215
00:17:32,751 --> 00:17:35,545
[NANBU] No effect! We just
don't have enough firepower.

216
00:17:35,628 --> 00:17:36,671
[KODAI]
Disengage!

217
00:17:36,755 --> 00:17:37,964
Huh...?

218
00:17:38,048 --> 00:17:41,092
Helm! Drop us down
directly below their stern.

219
00:17:44,929 --> 00:17:46,348
[KODAI] We're going to
push up on their keel

220
00:17:46,431 --> 00:17:49,601
to knock them off course.
Thrusters to maximum!

221
00:17:57,317 --> 00:18:01,738
[gasps] <i>Yunagi</i> , they've just
rammed the enemy ship!

222
00:18:01,821 --> 00:18:03,573
Be careful, Kodai.

223
00:18:07,869 --> 00:18:11,331
It's no use! We can't change
their line of descent!

224
00:18:18,713 --> 00:18:20,006
[AIHARA]
Captain, incoming call

225
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:22,509
from Lieutenant Mori
at HQ on a coded channel.

226
00:18:22,592 --> 00:18:23,593
From Yuki?

227
00:18:23,677 --> 00:18:25,095
[AIHARA]
Connecting.

228
00:18:25,178 --> 00:18:28,515
[MORI] Kodai, listen,
I'm patching you through.

229
00:18:28,598 --> 00:18:29,974
Captain Kodai.

230
00:18:30,058 --> 00:18:31,851
Wait, Sanada?

231
00:18:33,978 --> 00:18:36,773
[SANADA] Send us the enemy
vessel's course data.

232
00:18:40,318 --> 00:18:41,945
[KODAI]
Are you sure about this?

233
00:18:42,028 --> 00:18:44,114
We'll only have one chance.

234
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:52,247
[UNCF OPERATOR 1A] Evacuation
of third block is underway.

235
00:18:52,330 --> 00:18:53,748
Seventh block is released.

236
00:18:53,832 --> 00:18:56,001
Lowering platform now.

237
00:19:00,797 --> 00:19:03,008
Break away. Reverse thrusters.

238
00:19:03,091 --> 00:19:04,384
[NANBU]
Aye-aye!

239
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:07,220
Once again we'll have to
trust her to save all of us.

240
00:19:19,399 --> 00:19:22,027
[YAMAZAKI] Attention: all
workers in dock, board ship

241
00:19:22,110 --> 00:19:24,779
or take immediate shelter
in the evacuation block.

242
00:19:24,863 --> 00:19:28,241
This is not a drill. I repeat,
all workers in the dock,

243
00:19:28,324 --> 00:19:32,328
board ship or take immediate
shelter in the evacuation block.

244
00:19:32,412 --> 00:19:36,833
[DOCK WORKERS chattering]

245
00:19:38,293 --> 00:19:40,503
[ENOMOTO]
C'mon, c'mon! Move it!

246
00:19:47,510 --> 00:19:49,679
[TOKUGAWA] Auxiliary engine
system check complete.

247
00:19:49,763 --> 00:19:51,765
Holding charge at 100%.

248
00:19:51,848 --> 00:19:55,268
Circuits closed. Main cylinder
primed and ready.

249
00:19:55,352 --> 00:19:56,895
Start auxiliary engines.

250
00:19:56,978 --> 00:19:59,022
Starting auxiliary engines.

251
00:19:59,105 --> 00:20:00,940
Connect heavy power lines.

252
00:20:01,024 --> 00:20:02,942
Energy output at maximum.

253
00:20:03,026 --> 00:20:05,695
Weapons systems prepare to fire!

254
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:14,662
Rotation constant at 1600.

255
00:20:14,746 --> 00:20:17,499
Igniting auxiliary thrusters.

256
00:20:17,999 --> 00:20:20,752
Dock gantry locks, released!

257
00:20:22,712 --> 00:20:25,507
Let's go, men. Raise her up!

258
00:20:45,402 --> 00:20:48,029
[SANADA]
Angle of fire 35 degrees.

259
00:21:10,844 --> 00:21:12,595
Fire!

260
00:21:27,694 --> 00:21:30,447
We... We've been saved.

261
00:21:30,530 --> 00:21:32,240
Uh. Status report!

262
00:21:32,323 --> 00:21:34,242
Oh, yes sir!

263
00:21:34,325 --> 00:21:36,453
Enemy battleship
disappeared from radar

264
00:21:36,536 --> 00:21:39,289
at an altitude of 18,000 meters!

265
00:21:47,964 --> 00:21:51,217
They really did it.

266
00:21:51,301 --> 00:21:52,844
[KODAI]
Sanada.

267
00:22:06,649 --> 00:22:07,942
[UNCF OPERATOR 1D]
It's the <i>Yamato,</i> sir!

268
00:22:08,026 --> 00:22:10,153
That shot came from the <i>Yamato</i> !

269
00:22:10,236 --> 00:22:14,074
Is that possible? I thought
she was being remodeled.

270
00:22:14,157 --> 00:22:16,659
Get the undersea dock
on the line!

271
00:22:17,911 --> 00:22:19,913
<i>Yamato.</i>

272
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:33,635
[KODAI, NANBU, AIHARA gasp]

273
00:22:34,511 --> 00:22:36,137
[TOKUGAWA, SANADA]
Huh?

274
00:22:36,221 --> 00:22:37,430
What the...?

275
00:22:37,514 --> 00:22:39,724
What is this, what's happening?

276
00:22:41,476 --> 00:22:44,854
[KODAI]
Uh. Captain Okita!

277
00:22:44,938 --> 00:22:48,149
[OKITA]
Kodai, board the <i>Yamato.</i>

278
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,612
[OKITA]
Board the <i>Yamato.</i>

279
00:24:58,029 --> 00:24:58,947
[SANADA]
In my view

280
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:00,073
we're being called upon.

281
00:25:00,156 --> 00:25:01,074
[KODAI]
We should go!

282
00:25:01,157 --> 00:25:02,075
[KODAISHIMA]
And don't forget--

283
00:25:02,158 --> 00:25:03,410
you're not on your own anymore.

284
00:25:03,493 --> 00:25:05,787
[MORI] Fact is, I've been
happy for a long time.

285
00:25:05,870 --> 00:25:07,330
[KEYMAN]
Meet with Ambassador Burrell

286
00:25:07,414 --> 00:25:09,290
and you'll learn the truth
behind those visions.

287
00:25:09,374 --> 00:25:11,584
[KODAI] But for right now,
I just need to keep moving.

